<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 29 at 4:45PM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Band of Snow Leading to Slippery Travel This Evening...
A narrow band of light to moderate snow will move across portions
of eastern Iowa and northwest Illinois this evening into early
tonight. The steadiest snow is expected to fall approximately
between highway 30 and I-80, where accumulations of a half inch to
two inches are possible.
The snow will accumulate quickly on the cold pavement making for
slippery travel conditions. Visibilities could briefly drop to a
half mile in the heaviest snow. Please use extra caution if
traveling into early tonight.</description>
